cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SY, cs.SC 

The paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for cutting sets of lines and triangles in ${\Bbb R}^3$ into fragments that admit a depth order. This falls under the scope of computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of graphs (cs.GR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a refined bound that depends on the number of intersections between the projections of the triangle edges onto the $xy$-plane, which is related to the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SC).
